</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_F929F14E319F40F694D7003AB2AD32CB"><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead 3</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 04PH03 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">PBA</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_6E3F61EF57D54997889E5AEF1AD04145"><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead 4</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 04PH04 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">PBA</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_AB177A5D0B2A4B31B724BE06BE3DBE22"><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead 5</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 04PH05 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">PBA</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_FDA4EEE8FB3A47A1898ED2602F2E8811"><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead 6</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 04PH06 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">PBA</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li></ul></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_F9CA56DCBA8840BEBDE19FEF06E781CC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Cool down the printhead 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Cool down the printheads. Use 
<xref keyref="SDS04-6-015" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-62E0BD73-612D-486D-8BA5-A6CC3815A3E3.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04-6-015 Cool down printheads [Special Tests]?>04-6-015 Cool down printheads [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_53184B16D403439F881DA2AB90C20E0F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the top cover 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-7215619B-4D8E-42B1-B219-10C1EF6B5FB5" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not lean on the strip support. 
</p></note></li><li id="LI_26BBAC1869204A5181E4DF16E71533D0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="04DISA002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-75F1003D-F727-49BD-88A7-1CEF7223F097.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document?>04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document</xref> 
</p></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_65F6A9A2241848AF9B1AEB937C75B160" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_140FCE46ED0F42DDA169FF907B7DB406" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T6 
</p></li><li id="LI_380C014D7A5248799F47DC9499EBC17D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver small 
</p></li><li id="LI_D2F724326BA341EE8995AD7F4092F0C6" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">New boiler unit 
</p><fig id="FIG_23E7024985434330A70C88E7B15758B4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4A62C2C3-6443-47EE-A880-7A24F7F31B94-low.png" id="IMAGE_5C393176F55E4EF2885FEF73ED143557" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4A62C2C3-6443-47EE-A880-7A24F7F31B94-low.png"/></fig></li><li id="LI_FE40B2C129BC42978CDC6A6EEE5035E9" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Small blister 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Antistatic wristband 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-2D7D94A0-B26C-4C0B-B6A3-20C8621663A2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note><note type="important" id="GUID-19212FE1-0739-4D36-AE4D-49667AC5A182" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Use an antistatic wrist strap. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-1C6A5506-8461-4BFD-8B7C-FB47C7EF289A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8B4F6750-7BEF-4646-A431-8670A684BC0B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8B4F6750-7BEF-4646-A431-8670A684BC0B-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-759B6B00-9D33-42FE-BF9F-E5AA2C143E01" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-06C2BAB9-99EB-4457-9EC2-1B7E1BACE34B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-06C2BAB9-99EB-4457-9EC2-1B7E1BACE34B-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_2995D931C7564CDFB4DD418FBE8BB391" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Preparation</title><table id="TABLE_AF09A34517B949C58969BC24D65C036E" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Prepare the workspace. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_E3A54F4DA21E46CE88FE4C00BC3CB778" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7DBA753A-2EF3-46B7-9949-ADA29D946D02-low.png" id="IMAGE_9D74390AE3E5438298FCE4F5C6CEAAB8" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7DBA753A-2EF3-46B7-9949-ADA29D946D02-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the printhead in the small blister. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-1DB47B16-612F-4823-9CB1-E0E5C2A90A85" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Use the blister to protect the nozzle plate and other parts of the printhead. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-F8EE0CFF-8773-41B7-90FD-E8C20CAACB52" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0AA930E9-673B-4444-B30A-6F40202F6D7E-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0AA930E9-673B-4444-B30A-6F40202F6D7E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_E4038B7193ED41D5A1A851CB6ED2D114" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_1C1A0BB33CEA42E19CE41654BD2AD2D3" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the plastic cover (at the upper right hand side corner of the printhead). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-F0A7AEC8-1802-4D7B-888A-E99FC873E830" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-A93E7A86-481F-4693-99D4-AB786682048B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A93E7A86-481F-4693-99D4-AB786682048B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the plastic cover over the heatsink (Start at the right hand side). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-71FEECDF-434F-4366-8B66-2EDF2A563E76" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-A09E7836-1BD4-450D-80D5-1F8205601FB8-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A09E7836-1BD4-450D-80D5-1F8205601FB8-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the connector. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-CA784C6C-EF85-4199-A550-E2AF7B3CA394" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-F3F57066-E08F-4487-84BC-22C060C9D7D6-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F3F57066-E08F-4487-84BC-22C060C9D7D6-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the cover. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Unlock the 2 click fingers, and slide the cover to the opposite direction. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-82EE86DF-28FD-4A6C-82A7-F556F002325C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-599A77B8-68B8-402B-9989-35DBB34729C9-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-599A77B8-68B8-402B-9989-35DBB34729C9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the cable from the cable guides. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-C1CF7786-406B-441A-9553-9D77AB7A74DB" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-3859EAA2-3B39-470F-9B57-846CC503424C-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3859EAA2-3B39-470F-9B57-846CC503424C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 2 screws (Torx T6). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the boiler. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-A8B0EA5B-B0FC-4DAC-AC24-FDB08CDF3C81" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-AB3415F6-D5F5-4A9C-9A9A-5B9EA58EB0CF-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AB3415F6-D5F5-4A9C-9A9A-5B9EA58EB0CF-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the 2 O-rings with a small screwdriver. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-9E42E21B-0D31-4AA9-838E-8D3A8F8ABB3B" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-A6C30D99-8E61-4C34-B0AA-162B374789D8-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A6C30D99-8E61-4C34-B0AA-162B374789D8-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the ink tube is open. If needed: pierce the hole. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the ink spillage with a cloth. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the 2 new O-rings. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Bent the flex cable. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5A8D2846-4067-4B0E-8A6A-B54409B49199" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2DA96641-0A74-4FE8-8EBA-213DCAA27BD6-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2DA96641-0A74-4FE8-8EBA-213DCAA27BD6-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install in reverse order. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install the printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="04DISA002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-75F1003D-F727-49BD-88A7-1CEF7223F097.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document?>04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Mark the printhead with the replace boiler as empty. Use 
<xref keyref="SDS04-6-020" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-76FA0F98-276D-43D0-B9BF-6ABC38D906A7.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04-6-020 Mark printhead(s) as empty [Special Tests]?>04-6-020 Mark printhead(s) as empty [Special Tests]</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Calibrate: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="SDS21-6-002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D650BDBB-4674-4B96-BD64-98FDD9BAF4CB.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]?>21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> and select: <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Carriage Y calibration</ph>. 
